The paper deals with distributed consensus algorithms on graphs, which is a topic commonly studied in the systems and control community (cs.SY). The paper also discusses various types of stochastic disturbances, including transmission noise and quantization noise, which are topics commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT). The use of ordinary differential equations to analyze the convergence of the updates suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the mathematical aspects of control theory (cs.MA). The paper's focus on network-based consensus algorithms suggests that it may also be relevant to the field of network science (cs.NE). Finally, the paper's analysis of the asymptotic covariance and scaling of the asymptotic MSE suggests that it may also be relevant to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
